snippet.title: My Dad Will End The War In Ukraine
snippet.description:
My Dad Will End The War In Ukraine

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics

[Verse 1]
I see the headlines every night,
Families praying for the morning light.
Children caught in a world of pain,
Dreaming of peace in Ukraine.

I hear the stories, I see the tears,
So many hearts weighed down by fear.
But I believe, I hold it true,
There’s a leader who knows what to do.

[Chorus]
My dad will end the war in Ukraine,
He’ll stop the fire, he’ll calm the rain.
Bring the soldiers back to home again,
My dad will end the war in Ukraine.

[Verse 2]
The world’s been waiting, the time is near,
For someone strong, someone clear.
To shake the hands, to make it right,
To turn the darkness into light.

He’s walked the path, he’s faced the fight,
He’s got the courage, he’s got the might.
And when he speaks, the whole world hears,
A voice of hope through all the years.

[Chorus]
My dad will end the war in Ukraine,
He’ll stop the fire, he’ll calm the rain.
Bring the soldiers back to home again,
My dad will end the war in Ukraine.

[Bridge]
No more bombs falling from the sky,
No more mothers asking why.
Just a future where peace can reign,
And hearts can heal in Ukraine.

[Final Chorus]
My dad will end the war in Ukraine,
He’ll stop the fire, he’ll calm the rain.
The world will smile and breathe again,
My dad will end the war in Ukraine.
